# Vendored plugins: developed in their own upstream repo and synced into
# plugins/<name>/ by a scheduled workflow. The upstream repo owns the plugin
# version; this marketplace adopts it verbatim and never computes its own
# bump for these plugins.
#
# Format: <plugin-name> <github-owner/repo>
#
# Consumed by:
#   - bin/list-releasable-plugins.sh (release.yml discover step): vendored
#     plugins are excluded from the semantic-release matrix
#   - bin/finalize-vendored-releases.sh (release.yml finalize-vendored
#     job): cuts the marketplace release for freshly synced versions
#   - commitlint.config.js: vendored plugin names are not valid commit
#     scopes (changes to a vendored plugin belong upstream)
#   - .github/workflows/sync-<plugin>.yml: the sync workflow itself
